name: environmental-biotechnology-research-lab
notes: This laboratory supports aspects of the life cycle mission for ARDEC by investigating the performance of new treatment technologies to destroy waste streams from the production of energetics and warheads. This laboratory allows ARDEC to minimize environmental impacts and health risks while maintaining positive community relationship and environmental stewardship. This facility is available for partners within the government, private industry, and academia to perform screening of samples and for research, development, and demonstration of new technologies for energetic materials waste streams for both soil and water.

extras.value: This laboratory for environmental biotechnology for energetic life cycle study and green manufacturing is used to process operational, quality control and pilot demonstration process samples containing energetic material. The laboratory is used to conduct biological breakdown studies and environmental impacts of traditional and novel energetics. Capabilities for Green manufacturing using molecular techniques for biosynthesis are under development. To support these activities the lab has invested in strategic instrumentation for analysis of inorganic and organic materials critical to process monitoring and sample screening. Instrumentation includes the following:  Ion Chromatography(IC) Detection of Ions and Cations High Performance Liquid Chromatography(HPLC) Gas Chromatography(GC) Including Flame Ionization(FID) and Electron Capture Detection Biological Transfer Good Incubators
